parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight assembly can cause reduced visibility while driving at night, leading to accidents or near-misses, and potentially causing harm to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: Headlights are dim or do not illuminate
water or condensation inside the headlight housing
headlights flicker or go out while driving
difficulty seeing the road at night
and the need to drive with high beams on
which can be hazardous to oncoming traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Moisture in the headlights
headlight failure
low beam headlights not illuminating
water accumulation inside the headlight assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: Dashboard going completely black
gauge needles moving quickly back and forth
loss of power
electrical shorts
radio and interior lights not turning off
windows not opening or closing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof and liftgate can cause water leaks, electrical shorts, and injuries.
symptoms: Sunroof drain tubes dislodging
water leaking into the vehicle
liftgate opening or closing suddenly
liftgate not staying up or down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the vehicle to run out of fuel, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Defective fuel gauge
bearings falling out of the CV shaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Keyless Entry and Remote Start Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the keyless entry and remote start system can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Keyless entry module failing
vehicle not starting
idol saying "no remote detected".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to vibrate, sway, or lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or sways while driving
the rear axle service warning light illuminates
the traction control and stability warning lights illuminate
the vehicle makes abnormal noises
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the tires wear unevenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, stall, or jerk, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle loses motive power
stalls
or jerks
the clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the transmission warning light illuminates
and the vehicle vibrates or shuttering when downshifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause the vehicle to vibrate, make abnormal noises, and lose control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The front suspension makes loud noises
the vehicle vibrates
the tie rod ends and control arm are worn out
and the lubrication fittings are missing.
